There's a page missing, page 73.

20:14.300 --> 20:17.900
- Maybe it fell out.
- Pages don't fall out.

20:18.100 --> 20:22.100
Mr. Monk, it fell out.

20:23.400 --> 20:26.100
- It was torn out.
- It fell out.

20:26.200 --> 20:27.600
Stop it, stop it, stop it.

20:27.700 --> 20:29.900
No, no, mr. Monk, you don't
want to see page 73.

20:30.000 --> 20:32.900
- What, it can't be any worse than the rest of it.
- You wanna bet?

20:33.000 --> 20:35.500
- I have to know.
- No, mr. Monk, please.

20:35.600 --> 20:37.200
- Mr. Monk, please.
- It's my book.

20:37.300 --> 20:39.000
Let me see it.

20:39.400 --> 20:41.000
Let me see it!

20:41.100 --> 20:42.800
What are you doing?

20:42.900 --> 20:45.100
It's for your own good.

20:51.500 --> 20:54.600
That's $87.
Is this mastercard or--

20:54.700 --> 20:57.800
- Do you take cash?
- Sure, yeah, cash will do.

20:59.400 --> 21:03.100
- 85, 86, 87.

21:04.500 --> 21:06.100
- Great.

21:08.800 --> 21:12.300
- Do i know you?
- No, you do not.

21:12.800 --> 21:16.800
Okay, room eight
is just up those stairs.

21:52.900 --> 21:55.900
- 911
- Hello, i'm at the safari inn near the airport.

21:56.100 --> 21:58.000
Somebody...??

22:12.000 --> 22:14.200
We'll just be a little while.

22:14.500 --> 22:17.100
There she is.

22:22.900 --> 22:26.800
- Did anybody else know you were here?
- He must have followed her.

22:26.900 --> 22:28.500
Okay, so you checked in.

22:28.900 --> 22:31.200
I checked in.
I was walking to my room.

22:31.300 --> 22:33.500
He was right there.
He just came at me.

22:33.600 --> 22:35.700
- Did you see a weapon?
- A knife.

22:35.800 --> 22:37.000
He had a knife.

22:37.100 --> 22:39.700
He said, "i got you this time."

22:40.800 --> 22:42.700
I had a gun, my gun,
in my purse.

22:42.800 --> 22:44.300
I pulled it out.
I wasn't even thinking.

22:44.400 --> 22:48.200
I just closed
my eyes and bang.

22:48.800 --> 22:52.000
Hey, monk, you okay?

22:53.400 --> 22:55.900
Well, if you're not too busy,
the body's over here.

22:56.200 --> 22:57.200
Thank you.

22:57.300 --> 22:59.200
- So who was he?
- Ah, a nobody.

22:59.300 --> 23:01.900
Well, as close to a nobody
as you're gonna find.

23:03.300 --> 23:05.100
Timlinson.

23:05.200 --> 23:08.400
Yeah. We just ran his name.

23:09.200 --> 23:11.600
Never been arrested.
Not even a traffic ticket.

23:11.700 --> 23:13.300
Manages a taco bell.

23:13.400 --> 23:16.200
Before that, 15 years with
the city parks and maintenance.

23:16.300 --> 23:18.900
Before that, he was in the mail room
at some big accounting firm.

23:19.000 --> 23:21.400
Before that, a couple years
of community college.

23:21.500 --> 23:24.900
Under the radar his whole life
until about an hour ago.

23:25.100 --> 23:28.700
- And he wrote all those letters?
- Yeah, looks like it. We found more in his coat.

23:28.800 --> 23:32.200
Plus the handwriting matches,
at least to me.

23:32.300 --> 23:35.200
Plus he lives in sunset heights.

23:35.400 --> 23:36.700
That's where the other
letters were postmarked.

23:36.800 --> 23:38.600
Why would he do it?

23:38.800 --> 23:41.100
Maybe he loved the show.

23:41.800 --> 23:47.400
Maybe the show meant the world to him,
and she betrayed everything it stood for.

23:49.300 --> 23:51.300
He read the book, didn't he?

23:52.800 --> 23:54.000
Not page 73.

23:54.100 --> 23:56.800
- No, i ate it.
- Good.

23:57.300 --> 24:00.200
Miss rapp, do you
remember signing this?

24:00.300 --> 24:01.600
We found it in his car.

24:01.800 --> 24:05.900
- No, but i've signed millions of those.
I'll bet you have.

24:06.000 --> 24:08.600
Mr. Monk, thank you
for being here.

24:08.700 --> 24:13.900
- And you never saw this guy before?
- No. Maybe. I meet a lot of people.

24:14.000 --> 24:16.200
Yeah, we know.
We read the book.

24:16.300 --> 24:19.600
Maybe you should have called
your friend bob denver.

24:19.700 --> 24:20.600
Mr. Monk.

24:20.700 --> 24:24.200
I'm so sorry. He's never really
read anything like that before.

24:24.300 --> 24:26.300
- Can i take her home now?
- Yeah.

24:26.400 --> 24:30.100
We'll bring the car around front.
We'll deal with this tomorrow.

24:31.800 --> 24:37.600
- I'm sorry to disappoint you, mr. Monk.
- Is it true, the things in the book?

24:37.700 --> 24:41.200
The things--Things you did?

24:41.400 --> 24:45.800
- Not the whole truth.
- I knew it. I knew it. Thank god.

24:46.000 --> 24:47.900
I mean, i've done a lot worse.

24:48.000 --> 24:51.300
I mean, stuff i couldn't
even write about.

24:51.500 --> 24:53.500
I was young, mr. Monk.

24:53.600 --> 24:56.100
Weren't you young once?

24:57.100 --> 24:58.500
Right?

24:59.600 --> 25:01.100
Maybe you weren't.

25:01.300 --> 25:03.600
But you've been lonely.

25:04.600 --> 25:06.600
I can tell.

25:07.500 --> 25:09.300
I was just a girl, mr. Monk.

25:09.400 --> 25:14.600
Just a girl, trying to
be a little less lonely.

25:15.400 --> 25:18.800
I don't have a lot of
happy memories.

25:19.500 --> 25:23.300
Watching that show
was about it.

25:23.400 --> 25:25.200
Now it's gone.

25:25.400 --> 25:28.400
Well, if that's true,
i'm really sorry.

25:29.200 --> 25:31.300
Can you forgive me?

25:32.800 --> 25:34.400
No.

25:43.100 --> 25:45.800
Don't be mad. I know how you hate surprises,
so i'm just gonna warn you.

25:45.900 --> 25:47.300
I'm gonna be surprising you.

25:47.400 --> 25:50.000
- What? When?
- In about ten seconds.

25:50.100 --> 25:53.000
This is sort of a heads-Up,
like a surprise alert.

25:53.100 --> 25:57.700
Wait. You can't just burst in here
and say, "surprise alert."

25:57.800 --> 25:59.700
You have to give me
a little warning.

25:59.800 --> 26:02.100
Oh, okay, sorry.

26:02.500 --> 26:05.200
This is the surprise
alert warning.

26:06.500 --> 26:08.000
This is the surprise alert.

26:08.100 --> 26:09.500
Now...

26:12.900 --> 26:14.500
Surprise!

26:14.600 --> 26:17.700
I called ambrose, and he told me
this was your favorite snack.

26:17.800 --> 26:21.800
Ten round crackers, a glass of
apple juice with one ice cube.

26:21.900 --> 26:25.900
- What's going on?
- And i rented this, your favorite show.

26:26.000 --> 26:27.400
I don't have a favorite show.

26:27.500 --> 26:29.700
Mr. Monk, i know how important
this show is to you.

26:29.800 --> 26:31.800
Okay, you can still enjoy it.

26:31.900 --> 26:33.500
You can still watch it.

26:33.700 --> 26:34.900
All right, all right,

26:35.200 --> 26:36.800
You're 12 years old.
It's tuesday night.

26:36.900 --> 26:39.000
It's 8:00. You've been
waiting all week.

26:39.100 --> 26:40.900
It's cooper clan time.

26:41.000 --> 26:43.200
* make yourself at home
with the cooper clan *

26:43.300 --> 26:45.200
* you'll never be alone
with the cooper clan *

26:45.300 --> 26:48.100
* you got bill, janey,
cathy, and dan *

26:48.200 --> 26:49.400
* don't forget skip *

26:49.500 --> 26:52.900
- It's scamp.
- Scamp, get off that divan!

26:54.000 --> 26:56.800
You wasted your money.
I can't watch it.

26:56.900 --> 27:00.400
You know what, forget about christine rapp
and her stupid, stupid book.

27:00.500 --> 27:02.300
Everybody in hollywood's crazy,

27:02.400 --> 27:05.100
And if we think about that stuff,
nobody would ever to go the movies.

27:05.200 --> 27:07.300
- I don't go to the movies.
- Or watch tv.

27:07.400 --> 27:09.300
- I don't watch tv.
- You get the point.

27:09.400 --> 27:12.400
- No, i don't.
- All right, let's just try it.

27:12.500 --> 27:15.000
Let's just watch one.
Which one do you want to see?

27:16.000 --> 27:17.500
Let's see.

27:17.800 --> 27:19.600
"Where there's fire,
there's smoking."

27:19.700 --> 27:21.200
That sounds funny.

27:21.300 --> 27:26.400
"Slumber party pooper." "Grounded for life."
Well, i mean, they all sound fantastic.

27:29.200 --> 27:32.500
Okay. Let's just play
the first one.

27:46.300 --> 27:50.800
- Episode four, "broken arm, broken heart."
- Ooh, good choice. Episode four.

27:51.300 --> 27:54.100
* make yourself at home
with the cooper clan *

27:54.200 --> 27:57.000
* you'll never be alone
with the cooper clan *

27:57.100 --> 27:58.800
- Picture go fast.
- It just started.

27:58.900 --> 28:01.900
- Picture go fast.
- Go fast.

28:05.200 --> 28:07.100
??, picture regular.

28:07.200 --> 28:08.900
Picture regular.

28:11.300 --> 28:13.600
Hey, jimmy, you want
to sign my cast?

28:17.300 --> 28:20.100
Nobody groovy wants to
sign my cast.

28:31.700 --> 28:33.100
Picture freezer.

28:33.800 --> 28:35.500
Picture freezer.

28:37.400 --> 28:39.200
The "e" and the "t".

28:39.300 --> 28:41.300
- It's the same handwriting.
- As what?

28:41.400 --> 28:43.600
As the mirror and the letters
sent to christine rapp.

28:43.700 --> 28:45.700
I knew i'd seen it before.

28:45.900 --> 28:49.900
She wrote those letters to herself
with her left hand.

28:50.100 --> 28:51.700
Why?

28:58.500 --> 29:03.200
So she could kill victor timlinson
and claim it was self-Defense.

29:03.300 --> 29:04.800
She was setting him up.

29:04.900 --> 29:10.000
- You heard the captain. He was a nobody.
- Well, he was somebody to her.

29:12.100 --> 29:13.600
Hello?

29:14.700 --> 29:16.900
Hello, mr. Timlinson?

29:18.700 --> 29:19.900
I don't think he's home.

29:20.100 --> 29:23.200
Probably not. He's single,
and he's dead.

29:23.300 --> 29:25.200
Oh, yeah.

29:30.700 --> 29:31.700
Wait.

29:31.800 --> 29:33.300
Are you going in?

29:34.300 --> 29:37.000
- It'd be a crime not to.
- It'd be a crime if we did.

29:37.100 --> 29:39.200
So it doesn't matter either way.

29:47.500 --> 29:49.900
- Oh.
- Ew.

29:50.400 --> 29:52.700
- Don't touch anything.
- I'll try not to.

29:52.800 --> 29:54.900
I was talking to myself.

29:56.000 --> 29:58.400
Oh. So what are we looking for?

29:58.500 --> 30:02.300
A connection between
this guy and christine rapp.

30:02.400 --> 30:07.300
She killed him on purpose,
so they must have known each other.

30:09.000 --> 30:11.100
I don't see anything.

30:11.700 --> 30:14.700
Exactly. That's what's wrong.

30:15.200 --> 30:18.400
I mean, he was obsessed
with her, remember?

30:18.500 --> 30:20.100
Where are the pictures?

30:20.200 --> 30:22.900
Where's his cooper clan
lunch box?

30:23.200 --> 30:25.900
- There should be a shrine.
- Yeah.

30:26.100 --> 30:28.100
I'll go check in back.

30:35.800 --> 30:38.300
Interior decorating?

30:39.800 --> 30:42.000
I don't think so.

30:57.200 --> 31:00.700
Ballot

31:23.800 --> 31:25.200
Natalie.

31:25.500 --> 31:27.900
Natalie, look at this.

31:28.000 --> 31:29.600
I got it.

31:40.900 --> 31:43.200
You know, this was your mother's
favorite vase.

31:43.300 --> 31:44.800
It was a family heirloom.

31:44.900 --> 31:47.000
Do you know
what heirloom means?

31:47.100 --> 31:49.300
Easily breakable?

31:52.000 --> 31:55.000
Dad, you're a surgeon.
Why can't you operate on it?

31:55.100 --> 31:57.400
Wish i could, billy,
but i'm afraid in this case,

31:57.500 --> 31:59.600
The patient's never gonna recover.

31:59.700 --> 32:02.200
You all know the rules
about running in the house.

32:02.300 --> 32:03.700
We need to know
what happened here.

32:03.800 --> 32:06.000
Which one of you
broke the vase?

32:07.000 --> 32:10.200
Danny, do you have
something to say?

32:10.700 --> 32:12.000
Maybe it was a ghost.

32:12.100 --> 32:14.500
I always felt
this living room was haunted.

32:14.600 --> 32:17.800
The window was open.
Maybe a raccoon came in.

32:18.200 --> 32:21.200
I don't think it was a raccoon.
It's not a ghost.

32:21.300 --> 32:24.800
I think the culprit is
in this room right now.

32:25.000 --> 32:26.700
Why are you always accusing us?

32:26.800 --> 32:28.500
Why don't you ever
get mad at adrian?

32:28.600 --> 32:31.000
Yeah, you never
even suspect him.

32:31.100 --> 32:32.500
Adrian never gets in trouble.

32:32.600 --> 32:36.600
Adrian is perfect.
Adrian, adrian, adrian.

33:12.700 --> 33:14.300
Hey, mom. Hey, dad.

33:14.400 --> 33:17.600
Hey, danny. Hey, cathy.
Hey, billy. Hey, janey.

33:17.700 --> 33:18.800
Sorry i'm late.

33:18.900 --> 33:21.400
I was busy at school
because i'm so popular.

33:21.500 --> 33:24.900
Oh, guess what.
I made the football team.

33:26.200 --> 33:27.600
And guess what else.

33:27.700 --> 33:30.600
I'm the quarterback,
the popular star quarterback.

33:30.700 --> 33:34.000
And nobody makes fun of me
because i'm so popular.

33:34.100 --> 33:35.500
That's wonderful, adrian.

33:35.600 --> 33:37.400
Just don't throw
the ball around the house.

33:37.500 --> 33:39.200
- Oops.
- Why not?

33:39.300 --> 33:41.600
The vase is already broken.

33:44.200 --> 33:45.600
I'm so proud of you, son.

33:45.700 --> 33:47.300
Thanks for being
such a wonderful boy.

33:47.400 --> 33:48.600
You're welcome, dad.

33:48.700 --> 33:55.600
And thank you for never driving
away and leaving us forever.

33:57.300 --> 34:01.000
I would never do such a thing.
You don't have to worry about that.

34:24.199 --> 34:29.100
Cathy, is there anything
you'd like to say to mom and dad?

34:32.800 --> 34:35.600
Mom, dad,

34:36.000 --> 34:38.199
I have a confession.

34:39.199 --> 34:41.199
Scamp broke your vase.

34:41.400 --> 34:44.199
- Scamp?
- We didn't want to tell you.

34:44.300 --> 34:46.900
We were afraid you'd
send him back to the kennel.

34:48.800 --> 34:52.800
I understand why you did what you did,
but it's never right to lie.

34:52.900 --> 34:54.600
Sorry, dad.

34:54.699 --> 34:58.700
Cathy, is there anything else
you'd like to confess?

34:59.200 --> 35:01.400
I looked in janey's diary.

35:02.100 --> 35:04.400
No, no, you know
what i'm talking about.

35:05.900 --> 35:08.100
I'm talking about this.

35:08.400 --> 35:11.500
You mean, all the trophies
you won playing sports?

35:11.600 --> 35:15.200
Ha ha! No, not my trophies.

35:15.800 --> 35:19.300
I'm talking about her
silver globe award.

35:20.400 --> 35:23.100
You didn't really
earn this, did you?

35:23.500 --> 35:26.300
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Here's what happened.

35:26.500 --> 35:31.300
35 years ago, after this show was
cancelled, your career was in trouble.

35:31.400 --> 35:33.700
I'm not listening.
* la, la, la, la, la *

35:33.800 --> 35:38.000
And when you were nominated for this award,
you knew it was your last chance,

35:38.200 --> 35:41.400
And you would do
anything to win.

35:42.200 --> 35:45.200
You met a fan named
victor timlinson.

35:47.200 --> 35:49.000
He told you where he worked.

35:49.400 --> 35:52.500
It was the luckiest
break of your career.

35:52.900 --> 35:57.000
He worked for an accounting firm
called fineman and kelly.

35:57.100 --> 36:00.100
They tabulated the ballots for
all the big show business awards.

36:00.400 --> 36:02.700
Including...??

36:02.800 --> 36:08.000
He...???

36:08.400 --> 36:09.500
I don't know how you did it.

36:09.600 --> 36:12.000
Maybe you paid him off.
Maybe you flirted with him.

36:12.100 --> 36:16.000
But somehow you convinced him
to rig the final tally.

36:16.100 --> 36:19.200
Years went by. You probably figured
you'd never see him again.

36:19.300 --> 36:24.000
But when he read about your big
book deal, mr. Timlinson reappeared.

36:24.200 --> 36:25.900
He got greedy.

36:26.800 --> 36:28.700
He tried to shake you down.

36:28.800 --> 36:32.400
He threatened to tell the world
the truth about how you really won this.

36:32.500 --> 36:36.000
And you knew if you paid him,
he'd eventually want more.

36:36.100 --> 36:37.600
They always do.

36:37.700 --> 36:39.400
